# 🌽 CornLab: The Hypothesis Trial

> A production-level serious game for learning hypothesis testing through an agricultural simulation, integrating Gardner's Multiple Intelligences theory.

![Status](https://img.shields.io/badge/status-active-brightgreen) ![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.11-blue) ![FastAPI](https://img.shields.io/badge/FastAPI-0.110+-green)

---

## 📖 Overview

CornLab places the player as an agricultural data scientist investigating whether this year's corn yield has changed from last year. Through a 12×12 interactive field, players sample plots, visualize distributions, run hypothesis tests, and make decisions — all without needing any prior statistics knowledge.

Designed for **experimental research** with full A/B testing support:
- **Group A** — Full interactive game
- **Group B** — Static slide-based lesson (same content, no interaction)

---

## 🎮 Features

### Game
- 5 chapters with cinematic cutscenes and narrative progression
- 12×12 corn field with heatmap reveal
- One-sample t-test engine (pure Python, no scipy)
- Histogram with 95% CI shading and mean alignment
- NPC dialogue system (Farmer John, Dr. Smith, Policy Maker) with typing animation
- XP system, 5 levels, 8 unlockable badges
- Redo chapter mechanic
- Reflection journal

### Education
- Covers: H₀/H₁, p-value, confidence intervals, Type I & II errors, sampling
- Beginner-friendly — no formulas shown initially
- Tooltip system, hint system, step-by-step tutorial (Chapter 1)
- Gardner's Multiple Intelligences: Logical, Spatial, Bodily, Linguistic, Interpersonal, Intrapersonal, Musical, Naturalistic

### Research
- A/B testing mode (game vs. static lesson)
- Full behavioral data collection (clicks, time, hints, journal, decisions)
- CSV export endpoint
- Post-test assessment
- Fixed random seed for reproducibility

### Audio
- Procedurally generated BGM via Web Audio API — zero external files
- Sound effects: sampling, correct/wrong decision, reveal, hints, XP, dialogue blips
- Per-user on/off toggle with localStorage persistence

